cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL

This paper deals with brain tumor segmentation and survival prediction using deep neural networks and connectomics data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also uses machine learning techniques for survival prediction, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. The use of connectomics data and brain parcellation information suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) could also be a relevant category. Additionally, the paper involves feature extraction and analysis, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.CL (Computation and Language).
